name: 'Gourmet Scratch Map'
description:
A new word map product from Alison Hardcasle + Snowhome and in collaboration with Luckies.

We combined the Wordmap with their Scratchmap to create a scratchable word map which encourages you to eat your way around Europe’s signature dishess. Scratch off the food once you've cooked or eaten it. The Gourmet Scratch Map is beautiful in black but when you begin scratching the magic happens; reveal vibrant colours which demonstrate in no uncertain terms just how well rounded your taste buds are.

Gourmet Scratch Map has its own website at www.gourmetscratchmap.com so you don’t have to visit the country to try the food, just look up a dish on the website, buy the ingredients and cook it yourself.

An amazing gift for anyone who loves their food and their travel. 

Size:60 x 80cm
Material: Laminate, card and coloured foil.

name: Word Map Of London (Blue-Black)
description: Buoyed by the success of the British Isles Word Map this is the second collaborative print between Alison Hardcastle and Snowhome. This time we created a map reflecting the character of our most popular city - London. The intricate artwork provides a new perspective on London, with boroughs, communities and streets represented on the design by a word synonymous with that particular area. The outcome is a stunning visualisation of the city that celebrates the diversity, history and myth surrounding London through words and hand written type. It may not be an entirely reliable means of getting around the capital but it has certainly taught us a thing or two about London in it's creation! As with the Word Map Of The British Isles this started life as a list of carefully researched words and was then brought to life entirely by hand with a very small brush and a pot of ink. The end result was then printed as a lithograph. - A lithographic print which is printed on uncoated 200gsm paper - Packed in a tube. - 60x80cm (standard size ready-made frames) - Available in Blue-Black - Limited edition in Bus Red and Smoke Grey available here * Please note 20% VAT will be charged at check out on this item

name: Word Map of the British Isles (Blue-Black)
description: A collaborative print between Alison Hardcastle and Snowhome. The word map is made using selected text that has a certain relationship to its particular geographic location. The words used range from regional specialities to historical fact, from local celebrities to indigenous species. Stereotypes, clichés and typecasts help to build an archetypical map of text to chart the infinitely diverse character of the British Isles. Here typographic skills have turned jumbled lists of words into a lovingly hand drawn map which is as full of personality as the landscape that it covers. - A lithographic print which is printed on uncoated 200gsm paper - Packed in a tube. - 60x80cm (standard size ready-made frames) - Available in Blue-Black - Limited edition in Grey or Green available here * Please note 20% VAT will be charged at check out on this item

name: Word Map of the USA
description:
From hula to hot sauce and silver mines to silicon valley this intricate artwork provides a new perspective of the United States of America, with locations represented by words synonymous with their particular area. Stereotypes, clichés and typecasts help to build an archetypical map of text to chart the infinitely diverse character of the country.
The outcome is a stunning visualisation of America, one that celebrates the diversity, the history and regional intricacies of 50 states of which constitute the nation.

The Word Map of the USA was created in collaboration between design store Snowhome and illustrator Alison Hardcastle and is the third map in the series.

- A lithographic print which is printed on uncoated 200gsm paper
- Packed in a tube.
- 91.5x61cm
- Available in Blue-Black

* Please note 20% VAT will be charged at check out on this item

name: 'The Best Is Yet To Come' Alphabet Bag
description:
We've teamed up with Alphabet Bags as part of their brand new collection 'Artists For Alphabet Bags.' Featuring the ever-popular cut-out type of 'The Best Is Yet To Come' this bag is a wonderfully optimistic sentiment to have hanging from your arm!

Lovingly stitched and printed in the UK using terrific heavy weight cotton. 

- Made in the UK
- Heavy weight natural cotton
- Screen printed in olive green
- Mid-length handles
- 360mm by 420mm (14¼ by 16½ inches)

The Artists for Alphabet Bags Collection is an exciting collaboration between Alphabet Bags and some of their favourite artists! The collection will be ever-growing, bringing cheerful designs from incredibly talented artists from around the world to our sturdy cotton totes.

Alphabet Bags, brain-child of husband-and-wife team Lucas and Hayley, have seen incredible success since the launch of their brand 5 years ago. Built on the concept of simple, sweet, durable and functional cotton totes for everyday use, the bags are now carried in many major department stores across the UK and have a following around the world!

All Photos Courtesy of Alphabet Bags.
